com.bluegosling.possible

Class AbstractDynamicPossible<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.possible.AbstractDynamicPossible<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Possible<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Holder

    public abstract class AbstractDynamicPossible<T>
extends Object
implements Possible<T>
    An abstract base class for possible values that are dynamic, meaning whether a value is present or not can change over the life of the value. Possible values that are immutable should not extend this base class as they can be implemented much more efficiently due to their unchanging state.

    The default implementations in this base class are thread-safe and suitable for sub-classes that support concurrent usage. Where appropriate, this is handled by first checking the abstract Possible.isPresent() before calling Possible.get(). However, get() could still throw if the value suddenly becomes absent. So the implementations catch NoSuchElementException and then proceed as if isPresent() had returned false.

      • map

        public <U> Possible<U> map(Function<? super T,? extends U> function)
        Returns a possible that reflects the result of applying the given function to this possible value, if present.

        At any given moment, the returned possible is present if this possible is present. Similarly, for any given moment, the returned possible's value is the result of applying the given function to the value of this possible, if present. Since this possible's value is dynamic, the result of applying the function is not memo-ized. So the function may be invoked repeatedly by usages of the returned possible.

        Specified by:
        map in interface Possible<T>
        Parameters:
        function - the function used to transform the value
        Returns:
        returns the current value, transformed by the specified function, if present; otherwise returns a possible value that is absent

      • flatMap

        public <U> Possible<U> flatMap(Function<? super T,? extends Possible<U>> function)
        Returns a possible that reflects the result of applying the given function to this possible value, if present.

        At any given moment, the value of the returned possible will reflect the result of applying the given function to the value of this possible at that same moment. Just like with map(Function), the given function may be invoked repeatedly by usages of the returned possible.

        Specified by:
        flatMap in interface Possible<T>

      • filter

        public Possible<T> filter(Predicate<? super T> predicate)
        Returns a possible that reflects the result of applying the given predicate to this possible value, if present.

        At any given moment, the returned possible is present if and only if this possible is present and this possible's value matches the given predicate. Since this possible's value is dynamic, the result of applying the predicate is not memo-ized. So the predicate may be tested repeatedly by usages of the returned possible.

        Specified by:
        filter in interface Possible<T>
        Parameters:
        predicate - the predicated used to test the value
        Returns:
        returns the current value if present and it matches the specified predicate; otherwise returns a possible value that is absent
